  "riddle": "1. Unearth the story of a modern Indian statesman whose life inspired a cinematic portrayal. What day in the calendar did his film first grace the screens?\n\n2. High above the bustling city, within the park named after a famous observatory, lies an elevation reaching for the sky. What is the measure in meters?\n\n3. Seek the trail of a renowned musician known for intertwining the soulful sound of his voice with various languages. How many different tongues does his artistic repertoire encompass?\n\n4. A production house dedicated to cinema stands at the forefront of film making in India. Where does its headquarters rest upon the map?\n\n5. Delve into the heart of one of India's major metropolises, where the cityscape stretches upwards. How high is the land of this concrete jungle above sea level?\n\n6. This vibrant city also houses numerous repositories of knowledge. What is the total count of libraries that serve the local community?\n\n7. Before you proceed, combine the elevation you discovered about the metropolis from clue 5 with the number of libraries you counted in clue 6. What is the absolute difference between these two figures?\n\n8. Journey to a region where the postal codes reveal a multitude of medical institutions. How many hospitals are in proximity to the coordinates of 55.869?\n\n9. The digital realm welcomed a new streaming service that captured the imagination of many. What date marks its debut in the vast market of India?\n\n10. Zoom into automotive history, where a car's temperature gauge shifts from Celsius to Fahrenheit. What is the calculated offset when converting 19°C?\n\n11. As you ponder the figure from your automotive explorations, contemplate its prime essence. What is the largest prime factor of the number you found in clue 10?\n\n12. In memory of a revered leader, his years on earth were profoundly impactful. What was his age at the moment he departed from this world?\n\n13. Reflect on the longevity of this venerable figure and reveal the number of distinct divisors that his age at death presents.\n\n14. For the final act, sum the discoveries from clues 3 and 6, then compute the result of (19 + 20) modulo 10. What single-digit outcome do you unveil?",
